49// Global IOKit I/O registryID that can match a GPU across process boundaries.
50using IORegistryGPUID = uint64_t;
51
52// Code from WebKit to set an OpenGL context to use a particular GPU by ID.
53// https://trac.webkit.org/browser/webkit/trunk/Source/WebCore/platform/graphics/cocoa/GraphicsContextGLOpenGLCocoa.mm
54// Used with permission.
55static void SetGPUByRegistryID(CGLContextObj contextObj,
56 CGLPixelFormatObj pixelFormatObj,
57 IORegistryGPUID preferredGPUID)
58{
59 if (@available(macOS 10.13, *))
60 {
61 // When a process does not have access to the WindowServer (as with Chromium's GPU process
62 // and WebKit's WebProcess), there is no way for OpenGL to tell which GPU is connected to a
63 // display. On 10.13+, find the virtual screen that corresponds to the preferred GPU by its
64 // registryID. CGLSetVirtualScreen can then be used to tell OpenGL which GPU it should be
65 // using.
66
67 if (!contextObj || !preferredGPUID)
68 return;
69
70 GLint virtualScreenCount = 0;
71 CGLError error = CGLDescribePixelFormat(pixelFormatObj, 0, kCGLPFAVirtualScreenCount,
72 &virtualScreenCount);
73 ASSERT(error == kCGLNoError);
74
75 GLint firstAcceleratedScreen = -1;
76
77 for (GLint virtualScreen = 0; virtualScreen < virtualScreenCount; ++virtualScreen)
78 {
79 GLint displayMask = 0;
80 error = CGLDescribePixelFormat(pixelFormatObj, virtualScreen, kCGLPFADisplayMask,
81 &displayMask);
82 ASSERT(error == kCGLNoError);
83
84 auto gpuID = angle::GetGpuIDFromOpenGLDisplayMask(displayMask);
85
86 if (gpuID == preferredGPUID)
87 {
88 error = CGLSetVirtualScreen(contextObj, virtualScreen);
89 ASSERT(error == kCGLNoError);
90 fprintf(stderr, "Context (%p) set to GPU with ID: (%lld).", contextObj, gpuID);
91 return;
92 }
93
94 if (firstAcceleratedScreen < 0)
95 {
96 GLint isAccelerated = 0;
97 error = CGLDescribePixelFormat(pixelFormatObj, virtualScreen, kCGLPFAAccelerated,
98 &isAccelerated);
99 ASSERT(error == kCGLNoError);
100 if (isAccelerated)
101 firstAcceleratedScreen = virtualScreen;
102 }
103 }
104
105 // No registryID match found; set to first hardware-accelerated virtual screen.
106 if (firstAcceleratedScreen >= 0)
107 {
108 error = CGLSetVirtualScreen(contextObj, firstAcceleratedScreen);
109 ASSERT(error == kCGLNoError);
110 }
111 }
112}
113
114} // anonymous namespace

116EnsureCGLContextIsCurrent::EnsureCGLContextIsCurrent(CGLContextObj context)
117 : mOldContext(CGLGetCurrentContext()), mResetContext(mOldContext != context)
118{
119 if (mResetContext)
120 {
121 CGLSetCurrentContext(context);
122 }
123}
124
125EnsureCGLContextIsCurrent::~EnsureCGLContextIsCurrent()
126{
127 if (mResetContext)
128 {
129 CGLSetCurrentContext(mOldContext);
130 }
131}

133class FunctionsGLCGL : public FunctionsGL
134{
135 public:
136 FunctionsGLCGL(void *dylibHandle) : mDylibHandle(dylibHandle) {}
137
138 ~FunctionsGLCGL() override { dlclose(mDylibHandle); }
139
140 private:
141 void *loadProcAddress(const std::string &function) const override
142 {
143 return dlsym(mDylibHandle, function.c_str());
144 }
145
146 void *mDylibHandle;
147};

149DisplayCGL::DisplayCGL(const egl::DisplayState &state)
150 : DisplayGL(state),
151 mEGLDisplay(nullptr),
152 mContext(nullptr),
153 mPixelFormat(nullptr),
154 mSupportsGPUSwitching(false),
155 mCurrentGPUID(0),
156 mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat(nullptr),
157 mDiscreteGPURefs(0),
158 mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime(0.0)

163egl::Error DisplayCGL::initialize(egl::Display *display)
164{
165 mEGLDisplay = display;
166
167 angle::SystemInfo info;
168 if (!angle::GetSystemInfo(&info))
169 {
170 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Unable to query ANGLE's SystemInfo.";
171 }
172
173 // This code implements the effect of the
174 // disableGPUSwitchingSupport workaround in FeaturesGL.
175 mSupportsGPUSwitching = info.isMacSwitchable && !info.hasNVIDIAGPU();
176
177 {
178 // TODO(cwallez) investigate which pixel format we want
179 std::vector<CGLPixelFormatAttribute> attribs;
180 attribs.push_back(kCGLPFAOpenGLProfile);
181 attribs.push_back(static_cast<CGLPixelFormatAttribute>(kCGLOGLPVersion_3_2_Core));
182 attribs.push_back(kCGLPFAAllowOfflineRenderers);
183 attribs.push_back(static_cast<CGLPixelFormatAttribute>(0));
184 GLint nVirtualScreens = 0;
185 CGLChoosePixelFormat(attribs.data(), &mPixelFormat, &nVirtualScreens);
186
187 if (mPixelFormat == nullptr)
188 {
189 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Could not create the context's pixel format.";
190 }
191 }
192
193 CGLCreateContext(mPixelFormat, nullptr, &mContext);
194 if (mContext == nullptr)
195 {
196 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Could not create the CGL context.";
197 }
198
199 if (mSupportsGPUSwitching)
200 {
201 // Determine the currently active GPU on the system.
202 mCurrentGPUID = angle::GetGpuIDFromDisplayID(kCGDirectMainDisplay);
203 }
204
205 if (CGLSetCurrentContext(mContext) != kCGLNoError)
206 {
207 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Could not make the CGL context current.";
208 }
209 mThreadsWithCurrentContext.insert(std::this_thread::get_id());
210
211 // There is no equivalent getProcAddress in CGL so we open the dylib directly
212 void *handle = dlopen(kDefaultOpenGLDylibName, RTLD_NOW);
213 if (!handle)
214 {
215 handle = dlopen(kFallbackOpenGLDylibName, RTLD_NOW);
216 }
217 if (!handle)
218 {
219 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Could not open the OpenGL Framework.";
220 }
221
222 std::unique_ptr<FunctionsGL> functionsGL(new FunctionsGLCGL(handle));
223 functionsGL->initialize(display->getAttributeMap());
224
225 mRenderer.reset(new RendererCGL(std::move(functionsGL), display->getAttributeMap(), this));
226
227 const gl::Version &maxVersion = mRenderer->getMaxSupportedESVersion();
228 if (maxVersion < gl::Version(2, 0))
229 {
230 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "OpenGL ES 2.0 is not supportable.";
231 }
232
233 auto &attributes = display->getAttributeMap();
234 mDeviceContextIsVolatile =
235 attributes.get(EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_CONTEXT_VOLATILE_CGL_ANGLE, GL_FALSE);
236
237 return DisplayGL::initialize(display);
238}
239
240void DisplayCGL::terminate()
241{
242 DisplayGL::terminate();
243
244 mRenderer.reset();
245 if (mPixelFormat != nullptr)
246 {
247 CGLDestroyPixelFormat(mPixelFormat);
248 mPixelFormat = nullptr;
249 }
250 if (mContext != nullptr)
251 {
252 CGLSetCurrentContext(nullptr);
253 CGLDestroyContext(mContext);
254 mContext = nullptr;
255 mThreadsWithCurrentContext.clear();
256 }
257 if (mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat != nullptr)
258 {
259 CGLDestroyPixelFormat(mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat);
260 mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat = nullptr;
261 mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime = 0.0;
262 }
263}
264
265egl::Error DisplayCGL::prepareForCall()
266{
267 if (!mContext)
268 {
269 return egl::EglNotInitialized() << "Context not allocated.";
270 }
271 auto threadId = std::this_thread::get_id();
272 if (mDeviceContextIsVolatile ||
273 mThreadsWithCurrentContext.find(threadId) == mThreadsWithCurrentContext.end())
274 {
275 if (CGLSetCurrentContext(mContext) != kCGLNoError)
276 {
277 return egl::EglBadAlloc() << "Could not make device CGL context current.";
278 }
279 mThreadsWithCurrentContext.insert(threadId);
280 }
281 return egl::NoError();
282}
283
284egl::Error DisplayCGL::releaseThread()
285{
286 ASSERT(mContext);
287 auto threadId = std::this_thread::get_id();
288 if (mThreadsWithCurrentContext.find(threadId) != mThreadsWithCurrentContext.end())
289 {
290 if (CGLSetCurrentContext(nullptr) != kCGLNoError)
291 {
292 return egl::EglBadAlloc() << "Could not release device CGL context.";
293 }
294 mThreadsWithCurrentContext.erase(threadId);
295 }
296 return egl::NoError();
297}

341ContextImpl *DisplayCGL::createContext(const gl::State &state,
342 gl::ErrorSet *errorSet,
343 const egl::Config *configuration,
344 const gl::Context *shareContext,
345 const egl::AttributeMap &attribs)
346{
347 bool usesDiscreteGPU = false;
348
349 if (attribs.get(EGL_POWER_PREFERENCE_ANGLE, EGL_LOW_POWER_ANGLE) == EGL_HIGH_POWER_ANGLE)
350 {
351 // Should have been rejected by validation if not supported.
352 ASSERT(mSupportsGPUSwitching);
353 usesDiscreteGPU = true;
354 }
355
356 return new ContextCGL(this, state, errorSet, mRenderer, usesDiscreteGPU);
357}

364egl::ConfigSet DisplayCGL::generateConfigs()
365{
366 // TODO(cwallez): generate more config permutations
367 egl::ConfigSet configs;
368
369 const gl::Version &maxVersion = getMaxSupportedESVersion();
370 ASSERT(maxVersion >= gl::Version(2, 0));
371 bool supportsES3 = maxVersion >= gl::Version(3, 0);
372
373 egl::Config config;
374
375 // Native stuff
376 config.nativeVisualID = 0;
377 config.nativeVisualType = 0;
378 config.nativeRenderable = EGL_TRUE;
379
380 // Buffer sizes
381 config.redSize = 8;
382 config.greenSize = 8;
383 config.blueSize = 8;
384 config.alphaSize = 8;
385 config.depthSize = 24;
386 config.stencilSize = 8;
387
388 config.colorBufferType = EGL_RGB_BUFFER;
389 config.luminanceSize = 0;
390 config.alphaMaskSize = 0;
391
392 config.bufferSize = config.redSize + config.greenSize + config.blueSize + config.alphaSize;
393
394 config.transparentType = EGL_NONE;
395
396 // Pbuffer
397 config.maxPBufferWidth = 4096;
398 config.maxPBufferHeight = 4096;
399 config.maxPBufferPixels = 4096 * 4096;
400
401 // Caveat
402 config.configCaveat = EGL_NONE;
403
404 // Misc
405 config.sampleBuffers = 0;
406 config.samples = 0;
407 config.level = 0;
408 config.bindToTextureRGB = EGL_FALSE;
409 config.bindToTextureRGBA = EGL_FALSE;
410
411 config.bindToTextureTarget = EGL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE_ANGLE;
412
413 config.surfaceType = EGL_WINDOW_BIT | EGL_PBUFFER_BIT;
414
415 config.minSwapInterval = 1;
416 config.maxSwapInterval = 1;
417
418 config.renderTargetFormat = GL_RGBA8;
419 config.depthStencilFormat = GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8;
420
421 config.conformant = EGL_OPENGL_ES2_BIT | (supportsES3 ? EGL_OPENGL_ES3_BIT_KHR : 0);
422 config.renderableType = config.conformant;
423
424 config.matchNativePixmap = EGL_NONE;
425
426 config.colorComponentType = EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_FIXED_EXT;
427
428 configs.add(config);
429 return configs;
430}

481void DisplayCGL::generateExtensions(egl::DisplayExtensions *outExtensions) const
482{
483 outExtensions->iosurfaceClientBuffer = true;
484 outExtensions->surfacelessContext = true;
485 outExtensions->deviceQuery = true;
486
487 // Contexts are virtualized so textures and semaphores can be shared globally
488 outExtensions->displayTextureShareGroup = true;
489 outExtensions->displaySemaphoreShareGroup = true;
490
491 if (mSupportsGPUSwitching)
492 {
493 outExtensions->powerPreference = true;
494 }
495
496 DisplayGL::generateExtensions(outExtensions);
497}

550bool WorkerContextCGL::makeCurrent()
551{
552 CGLError error = CGLSetCurrentContext(mContext);
553 if (error != kCGLNoError)
554 {
555 ERR() << "Unable to make gl context current.\n";
556 return false;
557 }
558 return true;

576 return new WorkerContextCGL(context);

589egl::Error DisplayCGL::referenceDiscreteGPU()
590{
591 // Should have been rejected by validation if not supported.
592 ASSERT(mSupportsGPUSwitching);
593 // Create discrete pixel format if necessary.
594 if (mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat)
595 {
596 // Clear this out if necessary.
597 mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime = 0.0;
598 }
599 else
600 {
601 ASSERT(mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime == 0.0);
602 CGLPixelFormatAttribute discreteAttribs[] = {static_cast<CGLPixelFormatAttribute>(0)};
603 GLint numPixelFormats = 0;
604 if (CGLChoosePixelFormat(discreteAttribs, &mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat, &numPixelFormats) !=
605 kCGLNoError)
606 {
607 return egl::EglBadAlloc() << "Error choosing discrete pixel format.";
608 }
609 }
610 ++mDiscreteGPURefs;
611
612 return egl::NoError();
613}
614
615egl::Error DisplayCGL::unreferenceDiscreteGPU()
616{
617 // Should have been rejected by validation if not supported.
618 ASSERT(mSupportsGPUSwitching);
619 ASSERT(mDiscreteGPURefs > 0);
620 if (--mDiscreteGPURefs == 0)
621 {
622 auto *platform = ANGLEPlatformCurrent();
623 mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime = platform->monotonicallyIncreasingTime(platform);
624 }
625
626 return egl::NoError();
627}
628
629void DisplayCGL::checkDiscreteGPUStatus()
630{
631 const double kDiscreteGPUTimeoutInSeconds = 10.0;
632
633 if (mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime != 0.0)
634 {
635 ASSERT(mSupportsGPUSwitching);
636 // A non-zero value implies that the timer is ticking on deleting the discrete GPU pixel
637 // format.
638 auto *platform = ANGLEPlatformCurrent();
639 ASSERT(platform);
640 double currentTime = platform->monotonicallyIncreasingTime(platform);
641 if (currentTime > mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime + kDiscreteGPUTimeoutInSeconds)
642 {
643 CGLDestroyPixelFormat(mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat);
644 mDiscreteGPUPixelFormat = nullptr;
645 mLastDiscreteGPUUnrefTime = 0.0;
646 }
647 }
648}
649
650egl::Error DisplayCGL::handleGPUSwitch()
651{
652 if (mSupportsGPUSwitching)
653 {
654 uint64_t gpuID = angle::GetGpuIDFromDisplayID(kCGDirectMainDisplay);
655 if (gpuID != mCurrentGPUID)
656 {
657 SetGPUByRegistryID(mContext, mPixelFormat, gpuID);
658 // Performing the above operation seems to need a call to CGLSetCurrentContext to make
659 // the context work properly again. Failing to do this returns null strings for
660 // GL_VENDOR and GL_RENDERER.
661 CGLUpdateContext(mContext);
662 CGLSetCurrentContext(mContext);
663 onStateChange(angle::SubjectMessage::SubjectChanged);
664 mCurrentGPUID = gpuID;
665 }
666 }
667
668 return egl::NoError();
669}
